### Describe the bug

`fixperms` has messed up the execution permissions of all my files. Now I have to go one by one adding the permission back again.

### Expected behavior

There is no description telling me that this is going to mess the execution permissions. I was expecting it to change only the write permissions for the group and others.

This is what I was expecting:
```
# Fixes permissions for files and directories in the given folder or the current folder
fixperms() {
  find "${1:-.}" -type f -executable -exec chmod 744 {} \;
  find "${1:-.}" -type f ! -executable -exec chmod 644 {} \;
  find "${1:-.}" -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
}
```
